    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: HORTON ON/OFF - FAN CLUTCH "SYSTEM SENTRY"&#8482;</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FAN CLUTCH "SYSTEM SENTRY"&#8482;</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>Beginning September 1, 1993, International started phasing in an improved version of the on/off air
                engaged Horton fan clutch. While the new and old clutches are inter- changeable, the updated version's
                Piston Friction Disc is equipped with a "System Sentry" feature. The "System Sentry" per- forms as a
                fuse by reacting to clutch system faults to prevent overheating. The "System Sentry" is located on the
                outer surface of the piston friction disc (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200404">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200404" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200404" filename="../figg12/G1200404.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Old and New Style Piston Friction Disc</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. "SYSTEM SENTRY"</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BALANCE WEIGHT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
